### ── RESERVATION SERVICE (/reservation) ────────────────────────────────────
### Environment: Ctrl+Shift+P → Rest Client: Switch Environment → dev
### NOTE: use the reservationId returned from createReservation in subsequent requests.

### 1. Create reservation — Customer Bauer, Tesla Model 3 (BER)
# @name createRes
POST {{baseUrl}}/reservation/createReservation
Authorization: {{customerBauerAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "vehicleId": "40000000-4000-4000-4000-400000000016",
  "notes": "Bitte bis Freitag reservieren"
}

### 2. List reservations — Admin (all branches)
GET {{baseUrl}}/reservation/Reservations
Authorization: {{adminAuth}}

### 3. List reservations — Customer Bauer (own reservations only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/reservation/Reservations
Authorization: {{customerBauerAuth}}

### 4. Approve reservation — Operator
### reservationId: replace with ID returned from step 1
POST {{baseUrl}}/reservation/approveReservation
Authorization: {{operatorAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reservationId": "REPLACE_WITH_ID"
}

### 5. Double reservation on same vehicle — should be rejected (vehicle already RESERVED)
POST {{baseUrl}}/reservation/createReservation
Authorization: {{customerHoffmannAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "vehicleId": "40000000-4000-4000-4000-400000000016",
  "notes": "Doppelbuchung-Test"
}

### 6. Cancel reservation — Customer Bauer
POST {{baseUrl}}/reservation/cancelReservation
Authorization: {{customerBauerAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reservationId": "REPLACE_WITH_ID"
}

### 7. Cancelled vehicle should be reservable again
POST {{baseUrl}}/reservation/createReservation
Authorization: {{customerHoffmannAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "vehicleId": "40000000-4000-4000-4000-400000000016",
  "notes": "Jetzt wieder frei"
}
